## IIPS Application + High-Fidelity Plan
- **SentientOrchid focus (target)**: Enhance the viewer (or wrap via thin Orchid.tsx for "Sentient" personality) while keeping file in SentientOrchid/. Do not duplicate; evolve OrchidViewer.tsx + possibly update stub/index to re-export the sentient version.
- **Statemachine (idiomatic functional solid)**: Inside the component: `const [orchidState, setOrchidState] = createSignal<'idle'|'curious'|'happy'|'blooming'|'tickled'>('idle');` + derived signals (wiggleAmp, sparkleRate, smileOpacity). Use createEffect or on( state, ... ) to side-effect (trigger bursts, change anim params). No heavy classes.
- **Smile personify (cute pokemon-like)**: Add a charming smile that "blooms". Options (choose elegant): 2D DOM overlay <div class="smile">😊</div> absolutely positioned over canvas + use three Vector3.project + css left/top to follow a "face" point on model (or fixed sweet spot with subtle bob). Or pure three: small Torus/Line curve in warm pink that scales/rotates in on happy. Trigger on state change + tap. Make it feel alive and affectionate.
- **Wiggles or sparkles (threejs animations)**: In the RAF animate loop, react to state:
  - idle/curious: gentle whole-model sway + slow bob + occasional soft sparkles (small Point sprites or simple points orbiting or at tips).
  - happy/tickled: faster wiggle (sin on rotation.y + scale pulse on sub-group or whole), more sparkles, smile appears.
  - blooming: bigger slow opening scale + color shift on emissive or extra lights, particle burst.
  Add a tiny internal particle system (BufferGeometry points) for orbiting sparkles around the model — performant, disposed.
- **Better starting position + controls + touch-first**: Set initial controls {yaw: -0.6, pitch: 0.35, distance: 2.1} for a lovely 3/4 "looking at you" view of the orchid "face". Improve damping/momentum on drag release. Touch: already good; add visual "bloom" ring or subtle press scale on canvas down. Explicit "touch to wake" on load if idle.
- **Guided views + game-like interaction**: Inside the viewer container (glass framed), render a small row of touchable "view" affordances (solid buttons or hot labels): "Eyes", "Profile", "Under the petals", "Happy dance". On click: lerp/tween the controls values smoothly (use a simple accumulator or requestAnimationFrame lerp in the loop), setState('happy' or 'blooming'), trigger sparkle + haptic. Tap/hold zones on the 3d itself advance state ("tickle the orchid"). Make it feel like playing with a tiny friend that responds — reward curiosity.
- **Remove preceding scenes + Hadacard open mode**:
  - Add to Hadacard: prop `mode?: 'portrait' | 'open-letter'`, plus perhaps `onOpenComplete?: () => void`. When 'open-letter', trigger a one-shot or togglable "unfold" animation (e.g. via solid signal + style transform on .holo-card__inner : rotateX or scale + inner content swap to a larger flowing Pretext of the hbdMessage as the "letter inside", or a soft "page turn" via opacity + y translate of message area). Keep all holographic pointer magic. Default remains beautiful closed portrait for home.
  - Gift flow (circa + FrutigerScenes): Remove or bypass the "scenes that proceed" the orchid (the bubble pretext stage 1 + pop). Start the gift experience directly with the Hadacard in portrait, provide a clear "open your letter" affordance (the existing action button or the card itself). On open-complete, transition (with existing flash or gentle fade) to the enhanced sentient OrchidViewer as the living gift inside the opened letter. Preserve: time early/late guards, BGM audio (careful handoff), haptics, glass, particles (perhaps as "opening dust" or keep light version around orchid). This makes the experience "card -> open -> sentient orchid friend".
- **Solid + astro**: Keep heavy 3d + state in solid islands (client:load). Astro pages for shell + static guards.
- **VFS + reporting**: This review + the .programme (created as the loaded plan) + log updates + final history entry. Use .programme / .log / R-*.md as established typed names.
- **No new deps**: three + solid + existing utils only.

## Risks & Mitigations (High Care — No Mistakes)
- **Audio / scene logic**: FrutigerScenes owns BGM start/pause, global handoff, timers, timeStatus. Touch ONLY for removing the precede bubble stage + wiring hadacard->orchid. Never alter play/pause/resume.
- **Hadacard regression on home**: The home card must remain unchanged in appearance/behavior when no mode (or default 'portrait'). Open mode is opt-in for gift flow. Test build + mental (home still pretty 3d letter).
- **Three perf + mobile**: Current viewer is reasonable; added sparkles/wiggles must be light (few points, simple sin, no heavy geom every frame). Use existing dispose pattern. Test mental on touch drag + state changes.
- **GLB limitations**: No baked animations assumed. All wiggles/smile/sparkles are procedural (RAF + math) or 2d overlay. Smile must read as "part of the orchid" not sticker.
- **State machine scope creep**: Keep tiny (5 states max, drive 3-4 anim params). No complex reducer; signals + effects.
- **"Remove scenes" scope**: Do not delete the entire FrutigerScenes or particles (they are beautiful and were enhanced for "girly powerful" in prior authorized work). Collapse the precede logic for the circa gift path while leaving reusable pieces. If too destructive, provide a simpler direct orchid+hadacard-open path in circa and leave Frutiger for other uses.
- **Build / types**: Three types already there. New props on Hadacard must not break existing calls (home passes specific props, scenes will be updated).
- **Magic leak**: Every change judged by "does this still feel like a handwritten love letter with a living cute friend inside?" Wiggles should feel organic and affectionate, not game-y tech demo. Smile is the heart of personification — make it charming and subtle.
- **Cross-job**: Prior configs work already removed egift and put orchid at end; this mach2 refines per its specific bullets. Coordinate (don't revert prior).

## Alternatives Considered
- Full rewrite of gift scene into new component: higher risk; instead minimal edit to Frutiger or direct in circa + reuse.
- Bake smile into glb or new model: no (can't mutate asset); procedural/overlay wins for craft control.
- External animation lib or drei/solid-three: violates "in-project", minimal deps, IIPS. Pure three + solid signals is elegant here.
- Keep full visual novel bubbles: job explicitly says "remove the scenes that proceed that" — honor by collapsing precede for the orchid reveal.

## Exact Verification Steps (MANDATORY)
1. `cd web && bun run build` — clean exit 0 after every significant edit (post-orchid, post-hadacard mode, post-scenes change). Repeat at end.
2. Grep for residual "egift" (should be only comments in prior reviews/logs).
3. Mental runtime (gift path): /gifts/circa-1993 loads -> Hadacard (portrait) -> clear affordance to open (anim unfolds like a real letter) -> transitions to sentient orchid -> tap/tickle -> happy state, smile appears + wiggles + sparkles, guided view buttons change camera sweetly + advance state, touch drag + pinch still work, idle has cute sway.
4. Home unchanged: / still shows beautiful interactive Hadacard portrait with profile + message.
5. No console errors, haptics fire, audio continues (BGM).
6. .agents/ updates: this review, programme with live status, log appended, final history entry with decisions + "magic preserved".
7. Source touched only under components/ + the two gift files (authorized by job message).

